{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"final"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"naturalnocasecmpTo","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"_"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"to","kind":"internalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"String"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"text":"Int64","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:s5Int64V"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When used for sorting, natural order comparison orders sequences of numbers by the combined value of each digit as is often expected, instead of the single digit’s value. A sorted sequence of numbered strings will be "},{"code":"[\"1\", \"2\", \"3\", ...]","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", not "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"[\"1\", \"10\", \"2\", \"3\", ...]"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"With different string lengths, returns "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"1"},{"type":"text","text":" if this string is longer than the "},{"code":"to","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" string, or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"-1"},{"text":" if shorter. Note that the length of empty strings is ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"always"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"0"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To get a [bool] result from a string comparison, use the "},{"code":"==","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" operator instead. See also ","type":"text"},{"code":"naturalcasecmpTo(to:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"nocasecmpTo(to:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"code":"casecmpTo(to:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}],"abstract":[{"text":"Performs a ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"case-insensitive"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"natural order","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" comparison to another string. Returns "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"-1"},{"type":"text","text":" if less than, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"1"},{"type":"text","text":" if greater than, or "},{"code":"0","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" if equal. “Less than” or “greater than” are determined by the [url=https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/List_of_Unicode_characters]Unicode code points[\/url] of each string, which roughly matches the alphabetical order. Internally, lowercase characters are converted to uppercase for the comparison.","type":"text"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/StringName"]]},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/StringName\/naturalnocasecmpTo(_:)"},"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/stringname\/naturalnocasecmpto(_:)"]}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Instance Method","externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot10StringNameC18naturalnocasecmpToys5Int64VSSF","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"naturalnocasecmpTo","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","text":"String"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int64","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:s5Int64V"}],"symbolKind":"method","title":"naturalnocasecmpTo(_:)","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}]}